==Trivia==
*Though not explained in ''Old School RuneScape'', the boss's name originates from the [[rsw:Summer's End|Summer's End]] quest in ''RuneScape'': as the Spirit Beast was defeated in the Spirit Realm, a mirrored version of [[Gielinor]] where everything is opposite to the physical world and vice versa, the Corporeal Beast was incarnated in the physical world to replace the Spirit Beast in the spiritual world.
** Also explained in ''RuneScape'' is that the markings on the ground are the graves of the residents of [[rsw:Bonde Farm|Bonde Farm]].
* The magic area-of-effect attack the Corporeal Beast uses was originally named <code>[corp_sperm_splash]</code> in the game's code, though it was renamed to <code>[corp_magic_splash]</code> on [[28 October]] [[2020]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1449841608841736194|date=17 October 2021|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/103050|archivedate=18 October 2021}}
*[[Pet]]s cannot be brought into the Corporeal Beast's lair. Attempting to enter the cave while having one following the player will cause a message to appear in the chatbox, stating ''Your follower hides in fear and refuses to enter the cave.'' If the player attempts to drop their pet while inside, the chatbox will instead state ''Your follower hides in fear and won't come out.'' This is also a nod to ''RuneScape'', where the Corporeal Beast is capable of eating Summoning familiars, which are also followers.
*Corporeal Beast had a festive override wearing a [[santa hat]] during the [[2023 Christmas event/Gallery|2023]], [[2024 Christmas event/Gallery|2024]], and [[2025 Christmas event/Gallery|2025]] Christmas events.

